Looking at the accessibility tree, I can see that I'm currently on the product edit page for Maya Tunic. I previously modified the SEO settings by filling in the Meta Title, Meta Keywords, and Meta Description fields. I then attempted to save these changes by clicking on what I thought was the Save button (element 885), but it seems that element 885 was not actually the Save button.

Looking more carefully at the accessibility tree, I can see that the actual Save button is element 839, which is explicitly labeled as 'Save'. I should click this button to save the SEO settings I've modified.

```
[839] button 'Save'
    StaticText 'Save'
```

Let me click the correct Save button to save the changes I've made to the SEO settings for the Maya Tunic product.
